item.description:
@Dastan1 wrote:

[quote=“Remern, post:1, topic:367969”]I can make two users log on at the same time on my rsps and make them fight together and stuff…
Does this mean its online?
I use two different windows of the client and one on the server…[/quote]
You have to change the IP adress so that others could join your server.

The 2 different windows are your CMD window and a Client window.

CMD window is connected to the client which connects you to your server source which you can edit, etc.

item.title: Umm....Help?
item.dc:creator: @Uncalled Uncalled
item.description:
@Uncalled wrote:

If you can login, occasionally it means that the server is online.
But because you’re hosting it, it may mean that you can login and nobody else can.
I suggest using canyouseeme.org and typing the port you’re using.
If it says ‘Success’ in green letters, then you’re online.
